(1, 'Hysteroscopy:Medroxyprogesterone acetate 10mg/day, or Norethindrone acetate 5 mg / day, should be given for 10 to 14 days starting on 15th day of the cycle, following which withdrawal bleeding (medical curettage) will ensue', 0, 'H'),
(2, 'Hysteroscopy:The treatment is repeated for several cycles and can be reinstituted if a menorrhoea or DUB recurs', 0, 'H'),
(3, 'Hysteroscopy:In young women who are actively bleeding, any of the combination OCP can be given four times daily for one or 2 days followed by two pills daily through day 5 and then one pill daily through day 20; after withdrawal bleeding occurs; pills are', 0, 'H'),
(4, 'Hysteroscopy:In cases of intractable heavy bleeding danazol 200 mg four times daily is sometimes used to create an atrophic endometrium', 0, 'H'),
(5, 'Hysteroscopy:A GnRH agonist depot Leuprolide 3.75 mg I M monthly or Nafarslin 0.2 to 0.4 mg intranasally BD can be used for upto 6 months to create a temporary cessation of menstruation by ovarian suppression', 0, 'H'),
(6, 'Hysteroscopy:Symptoms of hypoestrinism are common and occur early in treatment, while use beyond 6 months is associated with significant osteopenia that is reversible when therapy is stopped', 0, 'H'),
(7, 'Hysteroscopy:In case of heavy bleeding, I.V. conjugated oestrogens 25 mg every 4 hours for three or four doses can be used, followed by oral conjugated oestrogen, 2.5 mg daily, or ethinyl oestradiol, 20 u.g daily, for 3 weeks, with the addition of Medroxy', 0, 'H'),
(8, 'Hysteroscopy:This will thicken the endometrium and control the bleeding', 0, 'H'),
(9, 'Hysteroscopy:If the abnormal bleeding is not controlled by hormonal treatment, consider D and C to check for incomplete abortion, polyps, submucous myomas, or endometrial cancer', 0, 'H'),
(10, 'Hysteroscopy:In women over age more than 40, a D and C or careful endometrial biopsy is generally indicated to rule out neoplasm before beginning hormonal therapy', 0, 'H'),
(11, 'Hysteroscopy:Endometrial ablation through the hysteroscope with LASER photocoagulation or electrocautery is an option; this technique is designed to reduce or prevent any future menstural flow', 0, 'H'),
(12, 'Hysteroscopy:NSAIDs like Ibuprofen, naproxen etc. often reduce blood loss in menorrhagia even that associated with IUD', 0, 'H'),
(13, 'Hysteroscopy:Prolonged use of a progestin (in minipill or in injectable contraceptives or in treatment for endometriosis) may also lead to intermittent bleeding sometimes severe', 0, 'H'),
(14, 'Here the endometrium becomes atrophic & fragile. If bleeding ensues it should be treated with oestrogens as follows:Ethinyl oestradiol, 20 microg / day for 7 days', 0, 'H'),
(15, 'Here the endometrium becomes atrophic & fragile. If bleeding ensues it should be treated with oestrogens as follows:Conjugated Destrogens 1.25 mg / day for 7 days', 0, 'H'),
(16, 'Here the endometrium becomes atrophic & fragile. If bleeding ensues it should be treated with oestrogens as follows:Stressful life situation / life styles and prolonged emotional turmoil or excessive drug usage / alcohol may contribute anovulation and DUB', 0, 'H'),
